<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="273" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2151/49.</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gummeré</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-24"><hi rend="italic">August 24,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>States that proclamation of Mouley Hafid as Sultan of Morocco and his
                                acceptance have been officially confirmed; that the new Sultan has
                                constituted his government and has been accepted by all southern
                                Morocco, including coast towns.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>